        <tr>
            <td width="25%" class="style3">
                <h3>
                    What is it</h3>
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style4">
                The world's largest online workplace, tapping into a global pool of qualified talent
                to hire, manage, and pay large teams.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style5">
                Traditional outsourcing using co-located offices to manage workers, typically located
                in a lower cost country.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style3">
                Assigning high volumes of small, low-value tasks to typically anonymous crowds.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td width="25%" class="style6">
                <h3>
                    Pricing
                </h3>
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style7">
                Percentage fee based on productivity.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" vclass="style8">
                Fixed infrastructure and fees including “middleman” markups.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style6">
                Lower prices for low-skilled work.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td width="25%" class="style9">
                <h3>
                    Quality assurance
                </h3>
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style10">
                Multiple quality levers based on testing, certifications, training, work history,
                feedback ratings.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style11">
                Interchangeable staff vetted by agency.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style9">
                Many people perform the same task on the theory that the most common result is the
                most accurate.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td width="25%" class="style12">
                <h3>
                    Worker connection
                </h3>
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style13">
                A direct connection to the team with the ability to hire whomever you want.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style14">
                Little to no visibility into who is doing the work.
            </td>
            <td width="25%" class="style12">
                By definition, work is done by anonymous crowds.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td width="25%" class="style15">
                <h3>
                    Operational flexibility
                </h3>
            </td>
            <td width="25%">
                Globally distributed freelancer network available on-demand for flexible ramp-up
                or ramp-down.
            </td>
            <td width="25%">
                Limited to vendor's geographical location(s) using a one-size-fits-all staffing
                model.
            </td>
            <td width="25%">
                Structured primarily for short-term, task-based projects.
            </td>
